"You can create and manage multiple encrypted databases.\n"
"\n"
"Use the sidebar to switch between them. Right-click a database to rename it, "
"set it as primary, or remove it from the list.\n"
"\n"
"The primary database is loaded automatically on startup."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:57
msgid "Organize with Groups"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:58
msgid ""
"Organize your tokens into groups for quick filtering.\n"
"\n"
"Use the dropdown in the header bar to filter by group, or search with the "
"“group:” prefix. Assign groups by right-clicking a token."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:65
msgid "Keyboard Shortcuts & Search"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:66
msgid ""
"Use Ctrl+N to add a token, Ctrl+F to search, F2 to edit, and Ctrl+? to see "
"all shortcuts.\n"
"\n"
"Desktop search integration lets you find tokens from GNOME or KDE without "
"opening the app."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:74
msgid ""
"Secret Service integration can store your database password in the system "
"keyring so the app unlocks automatically after login. It is disabled by "
"default.\n"
"\n"
"You can enable it and configure auto-lock in Settings → Security."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:81
msgid "Settings & Backup"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:82
msgid ""
"All preferences are in the Settings dialog, including countdown colors and "
"clipboard auto-clear.\n"
"\n"
"Back up and restore both your application preferences and your token "
"database from Settings → Backup, or via the CLI with --export-settings and --"
"import-settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:95
msgid "A Brand New Look"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:96
msgid ""
"OTPClient has been completely redesigned with GTK4 and libadwaita.\n"
"\n"
"The interface is faster, follows modern GNOME conventions, and supports both "
"light and dark themes natively."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:103
msgid "OTPs Are Now Hidden by Default"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:104
msgid ""
"Codes used to be visible at all times. They are now hidden so a glance at "
"your screen, a screenshot, or an Alt+Tab thumbnail no longer leaks them.\n"
"\n"
"Click a row to copy the OTP — it briefly appears so you can verify what was "
"copied, then re-hides. To restore the previous always-visible behavior, "
"toggle Hide OTPs by Default off in Settings → Display."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:114
msgid "Token Groups"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:115
msgid ""
"Organize your tokens into groups for quick access.\n"
"\n"
"Use the dropdown in the header bar to filter by group. Right-click a token "
"to assign it, or search with the “group:” prefix."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:123
msgid ""
"You can now manage multiple encrypted databases from the sidebar.\n"
"\n"
"Right-click a database to rename it, set it as primary, or remove it from "
"the list. The primary database loads on startup."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:129 ../src/gui/ui/window.ui:310
#: ../src/gui/ui/shortcuts-window.ui:4 ../src/gui/ui/shortcuts-window.ui:121
msgid "Keyboard Shortcuts"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:130
msgid ""
"Common actions now have keyboard shortcuts: Ctrl+N to add, Ctrl+F to search, "
"F2 to edit, and more.\n"
"\n"
"Press Ctrl+? to see all available shortcuts."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:136
msgid "Desktop Search"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:137
msgid ""
"Search from GNOME or KDE to find tokens across all your databases.\n"
"\n"
"In-app search also works across databases. Cross-database results show the "
"database name and are read-only."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:144
msgid "Security & Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:145
msgid ""
"Secret Service integration (keyring) is now disabled by default. You can "
"enable it in Settings → Security.\n"
"\n"
"Settings have moved to GSettings (migrated automatically). Back up and "
"restore preferences and your token database from Settings → Backup."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:153
msgid "And More"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:154
msgid ""
"Customize countdown colors in Settings. Drag and drop to reorder tokens. "
"Undo accidental deletions with a toast notification.\n"
"\n"
"Import encrypted backups directly in the app with inline password fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:168
msgid "Done"
msgstr ""

